Join us in Denver for the
2025 Collaborative Journalism Summit!

ENGAGEMENT

Prepare to partner in Denver.

The 2025 Collaborative Journalism Summit will be hosted in person in Denver on May 15-16, 2025! The Summit will feature two days of lightning talks, workshops, and participatory discussions about a wide array of #collaborativej topics and projects.

The Center for Cooperative Media at Montclair State University is hosting the 2025 Summit at Delta Hotels Denver Thornton. This year’s presenting sponsor is the Gates Family Foundation.

GET YOUR TICKET

The Summit is designed to be a fast-paced event full of sharing and learning. Both days are typically packed with sessions, so prepare accordingly.

As usual, the Summit has a Code of Conduct and Care policies and our Commitments pledge. Our commitments are driven by our focus on improving the inclusivity of the Summit and the diversity of its speakers and participants.

⭐ We require all Summit attendees to review our commitments and policies before you register.

 

Interested in sponsoring the Summit? Email Stefanie Murray at murrayst@montclair.edu

🦠 Important COVID-19 information:

We ask all individuals to follow current CDC guidance and adhere to the following policy:

  1. You must have not have been diagnosed with COVID-19 or have been reported as being symptomatic of COVID-19 to attend events in conference spaces.
  2. If you do not abide by federal, state, and local health regulations, the Center for Cooperative Media reserves the right to cancel your tickets to the event at any time.
  3. If you’re sick, don’t come to the Summit and get the rest of us sick.

Accessibility accommodations:

During the registration process, you will have the opportunity to let us know if you have any accessibility needs or would like to request any additional accommodations and we will provide what you need.

In the meantime, check out our #CollaborativeJ merch on our Bonfire store!

All proceeds from merch sales will support the Center’s collaborative journalism program.
